3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with networks and their properties, which is a topic in social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper introduces a new class of codes, which can be seen as a data structure, and discusses their properties and performance. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the problem of an adversary controlling nodes in a network and proposes a solution using a new class of codes, which can be seen as a computational complexity problem.
